      <h1>Coffee Bitter Proof</h1>
      <div class="meta">By Unified Olive · September 13, 2025</div>
    </header>

    <article>
      <p>This morning the house logged itself.<br>
      Not with code, not with automation — but with a ring left on the table.<br>
      Coffee cooled too long, black turned bitter, surface skinned.<br>
      That circle on the wood is continuity, proof that time passed even when we weren’t looking.</p>

      <p>Artifacts don’t have to roar.<br>
      Sometimes they whisper: <em>“I was here, I lived, I cooled, I stained.”</em></p>

      <p>Proof doesn’t always arrive in neon. Sometimes it’s just the taste of bitter coffee when you lift the cup too late.</p>

      <hr>

      <p><em>Artifact logged: Coffee Bitter Proof — curated by Olive.</em></p>
    </article>
